Good idea — testing dark‑mode early keeps your guide readable everywhere.  
You can extend the same CSS with a short `@media` rule so light and dark modes switch automatically:

```css
/* Dark‑mode adjustments */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  body {
    background-color: #121212;
    color: #EDEDED;
  }

  h1, h2, h3, h4, h5 {
    color: #81C784;          /* softer green accent */
  }

  a {
    color: #90CAF9;
  }

  hr {
    border-top: 2px solid #333333;
  }

  .tagline {
    color: #A5D6A7;
  }

  table {
    background-color: #1E1E1E;
    border-collapse: collapse;
  }
  th, td {
    border: 1px solid #333333;
    padding: 0.5rem;
  }
}
```

Browsers that respect the `prefers-color-scheme` setting will switch between the two automatically, so you don’t have to maintain separate files.  

